abstract: President Donald Trump on Tuesday said he had commuted the sentence of Rod Blagojevich, the former Democratic governor of Illinois convicted of corruption for trying to sell former President Barack Obama's vacated U.S. Senate seat.
snippet: President Donald Trump on Tuesday said he had commuted the sentence of Rod Blagojevich, the former Democratic governor of Illinois convicted of corruption for trying to sell former President Barack Obama's vacated U.S. Senate seat.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - President Donald Trump on Tuesday said he had commuted the sentence of Rod Blagojevich, the former Democratic governor of Illinois convicted of corruption for trying to sell former President Barack Obama's vacated U.S. Senate seat.
headline_main: Trump Cuts Prison Sentence for Illinois Ex-Governor Blagojevich
headline_print_headline: Trump Cuts Prison Sentence for Illinois Ex-Governor Blagojevich

abstract: Mr. Blagojevich, a Democrat and  former governor of Illinois, was accused of trying to sell the Senate seat left open when Barack Obama went to the White House.
snippet: Mr. Blagojevich, a Democrat and  former governor of Illinois, was accused of trying to sell the Senate seat left open when Barack Obama went to the White House.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Rod R. Blagojevich, whose criminal sentence President Trump has commuted, became a household name when he was arrested 12 years ago on an explosive accusation: Prosecutors said he had tried to sell or trade to the highest bidder the Senate seat that Barack Obama was vacating to become the president.

abstract: President Donald Trump went on a clemency blitz Tuesday, commuting former Illinois Gov. Rod Blagojevich's 14-year prison sentence and pardoning former New York City police commissioner Bernie Kerik, among a long list of others.
snippet: President Donald Trump went on a clemency blitz Tuesday, commuting former Illinois Gov. Rod Blagojevich's 14-year prison sentence and pardoning former New York City police commissioner Bernie Kerik, among a long list of others.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump went on a clemency blitz Tuesday, commuting former Illinois Gov. Rod Blagojevich's 14-year prison sentence and pardoning former New York City police commissioner Bernie Kerik, among a long list of others.
headline_main: President Trump Goes on Clemency Spree, and the List Is Long
headline_print_headline: President Trump Goes on Clemency Spree, and the List Is Long

abstract: Sen. Chris Murphy on Tuesday defended a weekend meeting he held with Iran's foreign minister in Europe, after his actions were questioned in conservative media andas President Donald Trump suggested they may have violated U.S. law.

abstract: The president also pardoned or commuted the sentences of eight others on Tuesday, including Edward DeBartolo, a former owner of the San Francisco 49ers.
snippet: The president also pardoned or commuted the sentences of eight others on Tuesday, including Edward DeBartolo, a former owner of the San Francisco 49ers.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, citing what he said was advice from friends and business associates, granted clemency on Tuesday to a who’s who of white-collar criminals from politics, sports and business who were convicted on charges involving fraud, corruption and lies — including the financier Michael R. Milken.

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump issued a pardon for Eddie DeBartolo Jr., the former owner of the San Francisco 49ers football team, a White House spokesman told reporters on Tuesday.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump issued a pardon for Eddie DeBartolo Jr., the former owner of the San Francisco 49ers football team, a White House spokesman told reporters on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump issued a pardon for Eddie DeBartolo Jr., the former owner of the San Francisco 49ers football team, a White House spokesman told reporters on Tuesday.
headline_main: Trump Issues Pardon of Former Owner of San Francisco 49ers
headline_print_headline: Trump Issues Pardon of Former Owner of San Francisco 49ers

abstract: The president, in a series of tweets, said the U.S. would not restrict sales to the country, a sharp shift in administration policy.
snippet: The president, in a series of tweets, said the U.S. would not restrict sales to the country, a sharp shift in administration policy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump publicly objected to efforts within his own administration to restrict the sales of American technology to China over national security concerns, insisting on Tuesday that such fears were an “excuse” and that the United States was open for business.

abstract: The president broadly asserted his authority of the criminal justice system, attacking law enforcement officials and issuing pardons.
snippet: The president broadly asserted his authority of the criminal justice system, attacking law enforcement officials and issuing pardons.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump and Attorney General William P. Barr agree on one thing at least: The president is making the attorney general’s job much harder. What they don’t agree on: Mr. Trump sees no reason to stop.

abstract: A Venezuelan teenager has been forced back to Mexico by U.S. government authorities who denied her claims that she was fleeing political repression and violence, even after they accepted the same claims from her father.
snippet: A Venezuelan teenager has been forced back to Mexico by U.S. government authorities who denied her claims that she was fleeing political repression and violence, even after they accepted the same claims from her father.
lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — A Venezuelan teenager has been forced back to Mexico by U.S. government authorities who denied her claims that she was fleeing political repression and violence, even after they accepted the same claims from her father.
headline_main: US Border Clampdown Forces Venezuelan Teen Into Mexico Alone
headline_print_headline: US Border Clampdown Forces Venezuelan Teen Into Mexico Alone
